@RRozak, in #4150 which entered master in 09e856d2f3721c77f537e5f98bdacd524349d2f9, this causes these two sv-tests below, that previously passed, to now core dump.  All other sv_tests pass as before.

third_party/tests/hdlconvertor/tests/sv_test/std2017/p137_2.sv
```
virtual class C#(parameter type T = logic, parameter SIZE = 1);
  typedef logic [SIZE-1:0] t_vector;
  typedef T t_array [SIZE-1:0];
  typedef struct {
    t_vector m0 [2*SIZE-1:0];
    t_array m1;
  } t_struct;
endclass

module top ();
  typedef logic [7:0] t_t0;
  C#(t_t0,3)::t_vector v0;
  C#(t_t0,3)::t_array a0;
  C#(bit,4)::t_struct s0;
endmodule
```

third_party/tests/hdlconvertor/tests/sv_test/std2012/p102.sv
```
virtual class C#(parameter type T = logic, parameter SIZE = 1);
    typedef logic [SIZE-1:0] t_vector;
    typedef T t_array [SIZE-1:0];
    typedef struct {
        t_vector m0 [2*SIZE-1:0];
        t_array m1;
    } t_struct;
endclass

module top ();
    typedef logic [7:0] t_t0;
    C#(t_t0,3)::t_vector v0; C#(t_t0,3)::t_array a0;
    C#(bit,4)::t_struct s0;
endmodule
```

Could you please look into these, and as always add a test_regress case to test appropriately (perhaps using above code)?  Thanks
